                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 1.  <span>Schematic diagram of PCR mediated Genomic DNA Splicing (GDS) strategy.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec2.fig1.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec2.fig1.caption1.p1"></a><p>Individual exons are amplified in the first PCR (exon PCR) following standard PCR protocol with software-optimized primers. A second PCR (overlapping PCR) is then carried out to join the exons and produce the full-length coding sequence. ATG and TAG indicate the start and stop codons, respectively.</p>
